  "body": "### Describe the feature\n\nWhen I try to run npx hardhat compile --show-stack-traces over a corporate proxy, I get the following error.  \r\n\r\nError HH502: Couldn't download compiler versions list. Please check your connection.\r\nCaused by: InvalidArgumentError: invalid protocol\r\nat parseURL (/path/node_modules/undici/lib/core/util.js:78:11)\r\n\r\nThis turned out to be due to having my http_proxy as http_proxy=proxy.company.com:port\r\nInstead, the undici library which gets called was expecting it to have http:// at the start. http_proxy=http://proxy.company.com:port/\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/nodejs/undici/blob/4885b11dd60b4d1a785c4e5a519ad87920549d1c/lib/core/util.js#L81-L83\r\n\r\nI don't think undici is willing to update their library, since this parseURL method could be used all over the place.  Instead an easy fix would be to append http:// to the http_proxy if it's not present.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/57c56d2353da8828d6b2c167b24bd70b6298a8cc/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/util/download.ts#L35\n\n### Search terms\n\n_No response_",
